1. task : discrete unit of work
2. task boundaries
3. Execution policy : what, when, where, how (of execution is specified)

4. shutdown / shutdownnow
5.callable, future, futuretask
callable better than runnable as we can throw exception

6. Tasks with an executor 
if not started :can be cancelled
if started : it depends how is reponsiveness to interruption handled

7. Future : get : blocks if not completed, but returns immediately, if complete or exception occurs )ExecutionException / Cancellation Exception)